<HEAD>With PM-Internment Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is the 257-156 roll call Thursday by
which the House gave final congressional approval to legislation to
provide payments and an official government apology to
Japanese-Americans sent to internment camps during World War II.
   A ``yes'' vote is a vote in favor of the legislation.
   Voting yes were 185 Democrats and 72 Republicans.
   Voting no were 56 Democrats and 100 Republicans.
   X denotes those not voting.
   Present denotes those who voted they were ``present'' at the
time of the vote but did not vote ``yes'' or ``no'' on the issue.
   There are three vacancies in the 435-member House.
</TEXT>
