<HEAD>Dollar, Stocks Up Slightly</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: LEADS with three grafs to UPDATE with dollar and stock
closings. Pick up 5th pvs, ``Activity during...'</NOTE>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The dollar inched up against the Japanese yen in
Tokyo trading Friday, while share prices on the stock exchange
posted moderate gains.
   The dollar opened the day's trading at 133.10 yen, up from
Thursday's close of 132.75 yen. It drifted slightly higher in
afternoon dealings and traded mainly between 133.03-133.28 yen
during the day. It ended the week at 133.12 yen, up 0.37 yen.
   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the Nikkei Stock Average of 225
selected issues, a 55.79-point loser the previous trading day,
added 130.72 points, or 0.46 percent, to close the week at
28,423.38 points.
   ``Activity during the summer is usually slow,'' said a spokesman
at a major Japanese securities firm. ``The index gains have been
small in view of a lack of any market-affecting news.''
   ``The market is almost directionless,'' said another broker.
Share prices ``are switching back and forth to rise and fall day by
day,'' he said, speaking on condition of anonymity.
