television and film producers.
   Guild leaders complained Thursday they had been forced by the
intransigence of the Alliance of Motion Picture and Television
Producers to accept a number of contract compromises.
   Nevertheless, guild members are expected to ratify the contract
Sunday. The writers say they can probably start work on a delayed
fall TV season by next week.
